This paper deals with distributed computing systems and coded computing techniques, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves coding theory and information theory concepts, which are studied in the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper presents a conceptual framework for partitioning work amongst nodes, which can be seen as a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms. The paper also discusses the use of statistical models for completion time, which can be seen as a problem in control systems (cs.SY) and networking (cs.NI).
